<DOC><DOCNO> AP891125-0131 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-25-89 2350EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-StoreFire     11-25 0191</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Store Fire,0198</SECOND><HEAD>Two Off-Duty Firefighters Extinguish Blaze in Store</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Two off-duty firefighters shopping in a crowdeddepartment store went into action Saturday when someone set fire toa pillow display, a fire chief said.   A plastic container filled with a flammable liquid was put inthe display at a Macy's store in the borough of Queens, thenlighted, said Fire Chief William Nagle.   Firefighters Bill Kregler and Wayne Wright happened to be in thestore shopping separately during the afternoon when they heardcries of ``Fire!'' and ran to help, Nagle said.   The two calmed frightened shoppers and tried to put out the firewith hand-held extinguishers. When that failed, they took over astore fire hose that two Macy's employees were unraveling.   By the time Nagle's crew arrived, the fire was out, the chiefsaid.   Kregler was taken to a hospital suffering from smoke inhalation,but was not seriously harmed said St. John's Hospital administratorCatherine Wilkinson.   The store's third floor was temporarily evacuated, but there wasno serious damage, Nagle said.   The fire was ruled arson and fire marshals were investigating,he said.</TEXT></DOC>